n	</div>\n	<div class=\"review-body\">I got my worst experience with this plugin in 2 years of wordpress development. There is no info given about its working. Couldn\'t find out which shortcode I need to enter. Read whole description on plugin page and documentation is total confusing. Worst documentation ever. Who was the great person who made this documentation... This guy don\'t have any sense of describing info regarding plugin on plugin page. All info shown plugin page is useless. He told only waste and kept hidden needed info. Don\'t waste your time on this stupid plugin. Go and find other plugin whose author has atleast sense of showing info of plugin.</div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"review\">\n	<div class=\"review-head\">\n		<div class=\"reviewer-info\">\n			<div class=\"review-title-section\">\n				<h4 class=\"review-title\">Works but error laden</h4>\n				<div class=\"star-rating\"><div class=\"wporg-ratings\" aria-label=\"1 out of 5 stars\" data-title-template=\"%s out of 5 stars\" data-rating=\"1\" style=\"color:#ffb900;\"><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-filled\"></span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-empty\"></span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-empty\"></span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-empty\"></span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-empty\"></span></div></div>\n			</div>\n			<p class=\"reviewer\">\n				By <a href=\"https://profiles.wordpress.org/archiseek\"><img alt=\'\' src=\'http://2.gravatar.com/avatar/eb224e84f75bb84669ddb917aae5c7a4?s=16&#038;d=monsterid&#038;r=g\' srcset=\'http://2.gravatar.com/avatar/eb224e84f75bb84669ddb917aae5c7a4?s=32&#038;d=monsterid&#038;r=g 2x\' class=\'avatar avatar-16 photo\' height=\'16\' width=\'16\' /></a><a href=\"https://profiles.wordpress.org/archiseek\" class=\"reviewer-name\">archiseek</a> on <span class=\"review-date\">September 19, 2017</span>			</p>\n		</div>\n	</div>\n	<div class=\"review-body\">It kinda works but the code is sloppy as hell, there are 404s all over the place and no real support.</div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"review\">\n	<div class=\"review-head\">\n		<div class=\"reviewer-info\">\n			<div class=\"review-title-section\">\n				<h4 class=\"review-title\">OK - but docs are confusing</h4>\n				<div class=\"star-rating\"><div class=\"wporg-ratings\" aria-label=\"3 out of 5 stars\" data-title-template=\"%s out of 5 stars\" data-rating=\"3\" style=\"color:#ffb900;\"><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-filled\"></span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-filled\"></span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-filled\"></span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-empty\"></span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-empty\"></span></div></div>\n			</div>\n			<p class=\"reviewer\">\n				By <a href=\"https://profiles.wordpress.org/aksteve\"><img alt=\'\' src=\'http://2.gravatar.com/avatar/5f6098c49f3b3f9ca2c252b76eebe452?s=16&#038;d=monsterid&#038;r=g\' srcset=\'http://2.gravatar.com/avatar/5f6098c49f3b3f9ca2c252b76eebe452?s=32&#038;d=monsterid&#038;r=g 2x\' class=\'avatar avatar-16 photo\' height=\'16\' width=\'16\' /></a><a href=\"https://profiles.wordpress.org/aksteve\" class=\"reviewer-name\">Steve <small>(aksteve)</small></a> on <span class=\"review-date\">September 18, 2017</span>			</p>\n		</div>\n	</div>\n	<div class=\"review-body\">The first thing you are going to want to know is \"where is the calendar\"?\n\nDoes it get automatically created? Do you have to create a page and insert shortcode? Do you have any control over what page the calendar goes on?\n\nBasic set up info.\n\nI have spent 30 minutes and can\'t find the answer. Not impressed.</div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"review\">\n	<div class=\"review-head\">\n		<div class=\"reviewer-info\">\n			<div class=\"review-title-section\">\n				<h4 class=\"review-title\">Junk !</h4>\n				<div class=\"star-rating\"><div class=\"wporg-ratings\" aria-label=\"1 out of 5 stars\" data-title-template=\"%s out of 5 stars\" data-rati