atar avatar-16 photo\' height=\'16\' width=\'16\' /></a><a href=\"https://profiles.wordpress.org/ahancock\" class=\"reviewer-name\">YesThatAllen <small>(ahancock)</small></a> on <span class=\"review-date\">September 15, 2017</span>			</p>\n		</div>\n	</div>\n	<div class=\"review-body\">I don\'t have an issue with the quality of the product so much as the shear number of products to purchase to get a working system.\n\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"review\">\n	<div class=\"review-head\">\n		<div class=\"reviewer-info\">\n			<div class=\"review-title-section\">\n				<h4 class=\"review-title\">Great app - Great Support</h4>\n				<div class=\"star-rating\"><div class=\"wporg-ratings\" aria-label=\"5 out of 5 stars\" data-title-template=\"%s out of 5 stars\" data-rating=\"5\" style=\"color:#ffb900;\"><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-filled\"></span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-filled\"></span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-filled\"></span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-filled\"></span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-filled\"></span></div></div>\n			</div>\n			<p class=\"reviewer\">\n				By <a href=\"https://profiles.wordpress.org/jb1337\"><img alt=\'\' src=\'http://2.gravatar.com/avatar/2b04473b3bc4cdfa52cdf4d2bfe2a8e0?s=16&#038;d=monsterid&#038;r=g\' srcset=\'http://2.gravatar.com/avatar/2b04473b3bc4cdfa52cdf4d2bfe2a8e0?s=32&#038;d=monsterid&#038;r=g 2x\' class=\'avatar avatar-16 photo\' height=\'16\' width=\'16\' /></a><a href=\"https://profiles.wordpress.org/jb1337\" class=\"reviewer-name\">jb1337</a> on <span class=\"review-date\">September 14, 2017</span>			</p>\n		</div>\n	</div>\n	<div class=\"review-body\">Very versitlie app with a lot of extras!</div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"review\">\n	<div class=\"review-head\">\n		<div class=\"reviewer-info\">\n			<div class=\"review-title-section\">\n				<h4 class=\"review-title\">Seems excellent but...</h4>\n				<div class=\"star-rating\"><div class=\"wporg-ratings\" aria-label=\"3 out of 5 stars\" data-title-template=\"%s out of 5 stars\" data-rating=\"3\" style=\"color:#ffb900;\"><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-filled\"></span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-filled\"></span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-filled\"></span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-empty\"></span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-empty\"></span></div></div>\n			</div>\n			<p class=\"reviewer\">\n				By <a href=\"https://profiles.wordpress.org/kirschrg\"><img alt=\'\' src=\'http://2.gravatar.com/avatar/b7c13f1af06667572fd817a67cb0e466?s=16&#038;d=monsterid&#038;r=g\' srcset=\'http://2.gravatar.com/avatar/b7c13f1af06667572fd817a67cb0e466?s=32&#038;d=monsterid&#038;r=g 2x\' class=\'avatar avatar-16 photo\' height=\'16\' width=\'16\' /></a><a href=\"https://profiles.wordpress.org/kirschrg\" class=\"reviewer-name\">kirschrg</a> on <span class=\"review-date\">September 7, 2017</span>			</p>\n		</div>\n	</div>\n	<div class=\"review-body\">Hello\n<strong>The Events Calendar Version 4.5.12.1</strong> free demo.\nIt looked perfect at first glance using the TOTAL theme default page settings but...\nAfter the initial setting changing some titles, and adding some events:\n\n1) I am <strong>UNABLE TO MODIFY the title</strong> like on any other page! A very annoying detail. I might have missed something or overlooked an important setting. Somebody may have done it ? Or the plug-in code should be improved on next release.\n\n2) After playing with settings, disable + suppress the plug-in and removing the tribe folder in the WP, I have <strong>empty pages</strong> when I click on an event in the calendar month view. The title is Nice but the text infos showing  up on mouse over the event have disappeared in the event page.\n\n3) <strong>Even more important</strong> : There seems to be no way to uninstall completely the plug-in in order to restart from scratch a new clean install. When I disable + suppress + install the plug-in, all the old settings and titles show up again. However it is a standard approach in a mixed-up situation, how can I force a complete new install from scratch ?\n\nThanks a lot for advice.\nRobert</div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"review\">\n	<div class=\"review-head\">\n		<div class=\"reviewer-info\">\n			<div class=\"review-title-section\">\n				<h4 class=\"review-title\">Great product - thanks.</h4>\n				<div class=\"star-rating\"><div class=\"wporg-ratings\" aria-label=\"5 out of 5 stars\" data-title-template=\"%s out of 5 stars\" data-rating=\"5\" style=\"color:#ffb900;\"><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-filled\"></span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-filled\"></span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-filled\"></span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-filled\"></span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-filled\"></span></div></div>\n			</div>\n			<p class=\"reviewer\">\n				By <a href=\"https://profiles.wordpress.org/officefocus\"><img alt=\'\' src=\'http://2.gravatar.com/avatar/b9a12e0b8bfcb89bd329813bbcfea4c7?s=16&#038;d=monsterid&#038;r=g\' srcset=\'http://2.gravatar.com/avatar/b9a12e0b8bfcb89bd329813bbcfea4c7?s=32&#038;d=monsterid&#038;r=g 2x\' class=\'avatar avatar-16 photo\' height=\'16\' width=\'16\' /></a><a href=\"https://profiles.wordpress.org/officefocus\" class=\"reviewer-name\">officeFocus</a> on <span class=\"review-date\">September 4, 2017</span>			</p>\n		</div>\n	</div>\n	<div class=\"review-body\">I\'ve been a loyal user through a few versions. It dies exactly what it promises.</div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"review\">\n	<div class=\"review-head\">\n		<div class=\"reviewer-info\">\n			<div class=\"review-title-section\">\n				<h4 class=\"review-title\">Development Heavy</h4>\n				<div class=\"star-rating\"><div class=\"wporg-ratings\" aria-label=\"3 out of 5 stars\" data-title-template=\"%s out of 5 stars\" data-rating=\"3\" style=\"color:#ffb900;\"><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-filled\"></span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-filled\"></span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-filled\"></span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-empty\"></span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-empty\"></span></div></div>\n			</div>\n			<p class=\"reviewer\">\n				By <a href=\"https://profiles.wordpress.org/ehlanafoley\"><img alt=\'\' src=\'http://0.gravatar.com/avatar/31332f3b8eaa6e8d0b6e05d0c9c4e59a?s=16&#038;d=monsterid&#038;r=g\' srcset=\'http://0.gravatar.com/avatar/31332f3b8eaa6e8d0b6e05d0c9c4e59a?s=32&#038;d=monsterid&#038;r=g 2x\' class=\'avatar avatar-16 photo\' height=\'16\' width=\'16\' /></a><a href=\"https://profiles.wordpress.org/ehlanafoley\" class=\"reviewer-name\">ehlanafoley</a> on <span class=\"review-date\">August 30, 2017</span>			</p>\n		</div>\n	</div>\n	<div class=\"review-body\">I\'ve spent all morning trying to figure out how to simply drop the calendar onto a page with a shortcode or embed. I\'m not a developer so this calendar isn\'t for me at all, really unclear instructions, will be looking elsewhere!</div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"review\">\n	<div class=\"review-head\">\n		<div class=\"reviewer-info\">\n			<div class=\"review-title-section\">\n				<h4 class=\"review-title\">Well Designed</h4>\n				<div class=\"star-rating\"><div class=\"wporg-ratings\" aria-label=\"5 out of 5 stars\" data-title-template=\"%s out of 5 stars\" data-rating=\"5\" style=\"color:#ffb900;\"><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-filled\"></span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-filled\"></span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-filled\"></span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-filled\"></span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-filled\"></span></div></div>\n			</div>\n			<p class=\"reviewer\">\n				By <a href=\"https://profiles.wordpress.org/akanning\"><img alt=\'\' src=\'http://1.gravatar.com/avatar/a70c8048b721f08fa99fadcfdcefb15f?s=16&#038;d=monsterid&#038;r=g\' srcset=\'http://1.gravatar.com/avatar/a70c8048b721f08fa99fadcfdcefb15f?s=32&#038;d=monsterid&#038;r=g 2x\' class=\'avatar avatar-16 photo\' height=\'16\' width=\'16\' /></a><a href=\"https://profiles.wordpress.org/akanning\" class=\"reviewer-name\">akanning</a> on <span class=\"review-date\">August 29, 2017</span>			</p>\n		</div>\n	</div>\n	<div class=\"review-body\">This is exactly what our organization needed for our internal website. It was easy to set up and even easier to maintain. A must have for any WordPress site!</div>\n</div>\n\";}s:13:\"download_link\";s:69:\"https://downloads.wordpress.org/plugin/the-events-calendar.4.5.13.zip\";s:11:\"screenshots\";a:12:{i:1;a:2:{s:3:\"src\";s:72:\"https://ps.w.org/the-events-calendar/assets/screenshot-1.png?rev=1679210\";s:7:\"caption\";s:21:\"Month View with Hover\";}i:10;a:2:{s:3:\"src\";s:73:\"https://ps.w.org/the-events-calendar/assets/screenshot-10.png?rev=1679210\";s:7:\"caption\";s:18:\"Events List Widget\";}i:11;a:2:{s:3:\"src\";s:73:\"https://ps.w.org/the-events-calendar/assets/screenshot-11.png?rev=1679210\";s:7:\"caption\";s:17:\"Mobile Month View\";}i:12;a:2:{s:3:\"src\";s:73:\"https://ps.w.org/the-events-calendar/assets/screenshot-12.png?rev=1679210\";s:7:\"caption\";s:12:\"CSV Importer\";}i:2;a:2:{s:3:\"src\";s:72:\"https://ps.w.org/the-events-calendar/assets/screenshot-2.png?rev=1679210\";s:7:\"caption\";s:10:\"Month View\";}i:3;a:2:{s:3:\"src\";s:72:\"https://ps.w.org/the-events-calendar/assets/screenshot-3.png?rev=1679210\";s:7:\"caption\";s:9:\"List View\";}i:4;a:2:{s:3:\"src\";s:72:\"https://ps.w.org/the-events-calendar/assets/screenshot-4.png?rev=1679210\";s:7:\"caption\";s:8:\"Day View\";}i:5;a:2:{s:3:\"src\";s:72:\"https://ps.w.org/the-events-calendar/assets/screenshot-5.png?rev=1679210\";s:7:\"caption\";s:12:\"Single Event\";}i:6;a:2:{s:3:\"src\";s:72:\"https://ps.w.org/the-events-calendar/assets/screenshot-6.png?rev=1679210\";s:7:\"caption\";s:12:\"Event Editor\";}i:7;a:2:{s:3:\"src\";s:72:\"https://ps.